casebody.data:
Robert Millette v. Frederick G. Reincke, Warden, Connecticut State Prison

King, C. J., Alcorn, House, Thim and Ryan, Js.

Argued February 6 decided February 6, 1969 Arnold H. Klau, special public defender, for the appellant (plaintiff). Thomas F. Wall, state’s attorney, for the appellee (defendant). *603Per Curiam.

The judgment is affirmed on the authority of Reed v. Reincke, 155 Conn. 591, 236 A.2d 909, D’Amico v. Reincke, 155 Conn. 627, 236 A.2d 914, State v. Gyuro, 156 Conn. 391, 394, 242 A.2d 734, and Williams v. Reincke, 157 Conn. 143, 147, 249 A.2d 252.

There is no error.
